The expansion of Othaya Level 4 Hospital may end in May, Health PS Nicholas Muraguri has said. He toured the hospital in Othaya town on Wednesday.Muraguri said it will be upgraded into a specialised regional hospital. So far more than Sh700 million has been spent on the expansion.&ldquo;In its phase II, it will bigger and better since it will serve more people than Nyeri Referral Hospital. It will be a facility for middle-level training of students from colleges and universities,&rdquo; he said.Muraguri was accompanied by MP Mary Wambui. He said a cancer centre will be put up. The hospital will serve people from Nyeri, Murang&rsquo;a, Isiolo and neigbouring counties, he said. It will have a 350-bed capacity.